sentences: Rickman was lead singer and drummer for Garaj Mahal from 2007–2011 and his rock band Big Mouth featuring guitarist Leonard Stevens.
He was also featured alongside Herbie Hancock, Wayne Shorter and Marcus Miller on the Tribute to Miles 2011 tour.

In 1989, Rickman traveled from his hometown, Washington D.C., to Los Angeles, CA at the request of his father, who introduced him to owner of Third Stone Records and American cinematic music director, Richard Rudolph.

Rudolph, known as "Dick" or to his friends and family as "Dickie" was the former husband of Minnie Riperton who Phil Upchurch, Rickman's father, had worked in the short-lived band, Rotary Connection in the 1960s.
In the early months of 1992, Sean returned to Washington, D.C. and began performing with DC area reggae band Blacksheep.
In the final months of 1992, Jamie Brown (owner of Sister2Sister Magazine) recommended Rickman to Kim Jenkins of Ardent Studios in Memphis, TN.
In 1993, Rickman again relocated to Los Angeles to perform with his father, veteran musician Phil Upchurch.
Producer Angelo Earl relocated to Los Angeles to work with him, but they both returned to their hometowns following a devastating 6.7 magnitude earthquake in January 1994.
In 1994–1996 Rickman began touring with Angela Bofill, and working on her album Love in Slow Motion.
For the years 1996 through 2002, Rickman toured and recorded four albums with Coleman.
In 1996 Rickman began touring with Maxwell.
In 1999 Rickman joined and produced albums with the group Dapp Theory.
He remained with Dapp Theory until 2007.
In 2000 Rickman toured with Meshell Ndegeocello (with keyboardist Peña) as well as performing on her album, Cookie.
In 2002 the DVD entitled Compositional Drumming was released, followed by clinics and lessons in the US.
In 2007 Rickman joined the fusion band Garaj Mahal and remained with the group until 2011.
In 2007 Rickman joined the fusion band Garaj Mahal and remained with the group until 2011.
In 2011 Rickman was selected as drummer for the Tribute To Miles 2011 European tour featuring Marcus Miller, Herbie Hancock and Wayne Shorter.
In 2012 Rickman re-united with Steve Coleman, which released Functional Arrhythmias.
In 2012 Rickman released his first solo album  One under his professional name "The Rick".
In 2013 Rickman launched his HD Video Lessons Website.
In 2014 Rickman launched his solo artist Music Website In 2016, Rickman released his second solo albu Zoom.
